1
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:37,954
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

2
00:00:54,512 --> 00:00:57,724
Stop interfering and go back
to where you belong, Hong Keum-bo.

3
00:00:57,807 --> 00:00:59,100
You did it all on purpose, didn't you?

4
00:00:59,184 --> 00:01:01,227
You intentionally put me on the task force

5
00:01:01,311 --> 00:01:02,645
and took those documents.

6
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:04,355
It's what you wanted.

7
00:01:06,232 --> 00:01:08,818
Wait. We're on a tight schedule.

8
00:01:08,902 --> 00:01:10,612
Don't we need a clerical assistant
for menial tasks

9
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:13,531
like coffee runs, copies,
and lunch delivery?

10
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:15,992
Please help out as much as you can.

11
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:20,872
DETAILS OF OUTSTANDING LIABILITIES

12
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:33,009
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

13
00:01:33,092 --> 00:01:34,719
I've gotten in touch with
an overseas investment firm

14
00:01:34,803 --> 00:01:36,596
that can provide short-term funding.

15
00:01:36,679 --> 00:01:38,515
It's called DK Ventures,

16
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:40,308
and they'll be in Seoul for due diligence.

17
00:01:40,391 --> 00:01:43,895
What if they try to assert their leverage
to strong-arm us?

18
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:45,271
There's no need for concern.

19
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:47,565
I believe this is where my role comes in.

20
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:50,276
I'll handle the negotiations
to ensure the terms are favorable for us.

21
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:54,739
All right. Excellent.

22
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:55,740
Come in.

23
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,498
President Shin.

24
00:02:03,581 --> 00:02:08,128
Let Ms. Song know
once the investor confirms their flight.

25
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:12,382
We must show our special guests
the warmest hospitality.

26
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:13,341
Yes, sir.

27
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:15,260
I'll let her know as soon as possible.

28
00:02:15,343 --> 00:02:16,177
Good.

29
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:29,566
Ms. Song.

30
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:33,236
Do you know why I chose to appoint

31
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:36,030
Shin Jung-woo as the president of Hanmin?

32
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:40,994
He reached out first back then.

33
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:45,248
I remember he sent his condolences
when President Kang passed away.

34
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:46,958
Condolences were just an excuse.

35
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,544
That's how he asserted his presence to me.

36
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:54,173
I was also like that when I was younger.

37
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:57,468
Shin has agreed to introduce us
to an investor,

38
00:02:57,552 --> 00:02:59,220
so we must take advantage of that.

39
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:02,765
Sir, are you also considering
President Shin

40
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:05,894
as a potential son-in-law,
as Madam Choi does?

41
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:08,229
We'll have to see
if he's got what it takes.

42
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:11,024
Right.

43
00:03:11,649 --> 00:03:15,153
About the hidden Swiss bank account
under Nora's name…

44
00:03:15,236 --> 00:03:19,866
Are you certain she and her mother
are still in the dark about it?

45
00:03:19,949 --> 00:03:23,411
You and I are the only ones
who know about that account.

46
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:24,412
All right.

47
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:28,750
It's time I bring Nora into my house.

48
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:31,461
A storm is coming,

49
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:35,256
so let us fortify the granary first.

50
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:36,174
All right?

51
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:44,390
{\an8}FOR LEASE

52
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:50,855
{\an8}Jeez, what is happening
to this country's economy?

53
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:52,649
{\an8}CLOSING NOTICE

54
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:55,235
{\an8}- Two orders of noodles for you.
- Thank you.

55
00:03:58,488 --> 00:04:01,407
{\an8}I told you to go easy on Yehppee
and coax him,

56
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:02,742
{\an8}not finish him off.

57
00:04:04,118 --> 00:04:06,663
{\an8}Then should I have helped them
with the hidden slush fund

58
00:04:06,746 --> 00:04:08,623
{\an8}and shamelessly looted
the taxpayers' money?

59
00:04:08,706 --> 00:04:11,125
{\an8}Bang Jin-mok wasn't wrong, you know.

60
00:04:11,209 --> 00:04:13,795
{\an8}Even if the IMF crisis makes
Hanmin falter now,

61
00:04:13,878 --> 00:04:16,172
{\an8}Chairman Kang won't be affected
in the slightest.

62
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:19,550
{\an8}Only the innocent employees
will suffer the hit and fallout.

63
00:04:19,634 --> 00:04:21,511
I think Shin Jung-woo
was onto our investigation

64
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:22,971
and sabotaged it on purpose.

65
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:26,057
He knew exactly what he was doing

66
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:29,310
when he put me on that task force
and took the document I prepared.

67
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,021
It's still too early
to jump to conclusions.

68
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:33,564
If he wanted to score major points,

69
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:36,317
he would've simply handed you over
to Chairman Kang.

70
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,111
Who knows?

71
00:04:38,194 --> 00:04:41,781
Shin Jung-woo might be helping you out
without you knowing,

72
00:04:41,864 --> 00:04:43,157
just like he did in the past.

73
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:44,575
What do you mean?

74
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:45,994
When did he ever help me?

75
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,079
{\an8}Firing her for whistleblowing alone…

76
00:04:48,162 --> 00:04:48,997
{\an8}9 YEARS AGO, 1988

77
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,456
…would be enough to send a warning

78
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,625
not just to Hong Keum-bo,
but to the whole office.

79
00:04:52,709 --> 00:04:56,337
And if she leaks those files she has?
What then?

80
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:57,588
That won't happen,

81
00:04:57,672 --> 00:04:59,090
and I'll take responsibility
if it ever does.

82
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:01,718
Even now, the company needs people
to do the work.

83
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,178
I'll take over…

84
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:06,347
the work Mr. Yun was doing.

85
00:05:07,598 --> 00:05:09,642
Please just drop the lawsuit
against Hong Keum-bo.

86
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,980
<i>Back then,</i>

87
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:17,066
Shin Jung-woo ran around
as if his life depended on it

88
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,444
to stop your old firm
from pursuing a retaliatory lawsuit.

89
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:22,989
Why the hell didn't you tell me sooner?

90
00:05:25,116 --> 00:05:26,075
That scared me.

91
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:28,244
Don't get mad at me.

92
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:34,000
What if you had known sooner?
Would that have changed anything?

93
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,880
I guess deep down you still have

94
00:05:39,964 --> 00:05:41,507
at least a spoonful of hope left for him.

95
00:05:43,092 --> 00:05:44,218
Hope, my ass.

96
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:46,137
Why would he bother to help me?

97
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:47,972
He's about to marry into the Kang family.

98
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:49,557
You think he'd walk away
from that opportunity?

99
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,226
Damn it.

100
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:53,936
You have a point.

101
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:58,900
Anyway, all signs point to us
ending the operation.

102
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:00,401
Let's wrap it up.

103
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:09,452
I mean,

104
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,996
you went undercover to expose

105
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:15,166
corruption within Hanmin's ownership
and management.

106
00:06:16,334 --> 00:06:20,129
The livelihoods of its employees
aren't our responsibility.

107
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:23,633
Besides, we're barely
keeping our heads above water as it is.

108
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:25,927
They're talking about
financial reform laws and whatnot

109
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:28,471
and even possibly disbanding the FSS.

110
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,640
Talk of restructuring
has everyone feeling uneasy,

111
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:33,810
so you'll return to the office
by December 8th at the latest.

112
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:38,439
You pay for that.

113
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:57,875
Amid the worst economic crisis in history,
stock prices have hit a ten-year low.

114
00:06:58,459 --> 00:06:59,627
<i>Banks and securities firms</i>

115
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:03,506
<i>are being hit by waves of withdrawals</i>
<i>and intense client backlash.</i>

116
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:07,135
<i>Clients hoping to withdraw their funds</i>
<i>have been gathering in droves</i>

117
00:07:07,218 --> 00:07:09,637
<i>at these financial institutions,</i>
<i>even before business hours.</i>

118
00:07:15,143 --> 00:07:17,437
CRIMINAL COMPLAINT:
FRAUD

119
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:21,566
{\an8}DEFENDANT: KIM MI-SOOK

120
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:25,111
{\an8}THE COMPLAINANT SEEKS DAMAGES
FOR FINANCIAL LOSSES…

121
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:35,746
Did you hear?

122
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,081
The branch manager's playing dumb again.

123
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:38,958
Even the head office made it clear

124
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:41,669
that the employees are responsible
for the funds they sold.

125
00:07:41,752 --> 00:07:44,297
At our branch,
Kim Mi-sook is in the most trouble.

126
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,174
I hear she even received
a criminal complaint.

127
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:47,758
How could she possibly
compensate them all?

128
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:48,718
She's done for.

129
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:51,220
At least she's a single woman
without kids.

130
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,431
You know those debts can be passed down.

131
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:56,267
I know, right?

132
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:19,874
I knew it.

133
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:21,626
I clearly have an eye for these things.

134
00:08:22,126 --> 00:08:24,504
Let's accentuate that waist a bit more.

135
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:31,677
Mom, I just snuck out briefly
during my lunch break.

136
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:34,597
I told you earlier, right?

137
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:36,599
My daughter's being trained as an heiress.

138
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:39,977
We should start bride lessons soon too.

139
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:41,437
Oh, right.

140
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:44,106
Nora, let's move you into Dad's place
as soon as possible.

141
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:48,236
Your dad gave a special order
for you to move in.

142
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,113
Albert has been living it up

143
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:54,033
in your dad's palace of a house
all this time,

144
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:58,496
while you've been crammed into
that shoebox with three others.

145
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,289
It upsets me so much.

146
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:02,833
There are five of us, not four.

147
00:09:03,584 --> 00:09:05,336
What? Five?

148
00:09:05,419 --> 00:09:06,754
What? It's nothing.

149
00:09:08,506 --> 00:09:10,466
I think we should
lower the shoulders a bit.

150
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:12,760
It's so pretty.

151
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:13,844
This side too.

152
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:22,853
<i>Hong Jang-mi is actually Hong Keum-bo,</i>

153
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:25,106
<i>and Hong Keum-bo works for the FSS.</i>

154
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:29,360
<i>The FSS was in charge of</i>
<i>investigating Hanmin's slush fund,</i>

155
00:09:29,443 --> 00:09:32,446
<i>so did Hong Keum-bo lie her way in here</i>
<i>to dig into the slush fund?</i>

156
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:34,282
<i>Is that why…</i>

157
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:36,242
<i>Where did you get that notebook from?</i>

158
00:09:36,325 --> 00:09:38,160
You took it from the president's office.

159
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,121
Did you take it knowing about the raid?

160
00:09:40,204 --> 00:09:41,330
Who told you to?

161
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,373
<i>Hold on.</i>

162
00:09:42,873 --> 00:09:45,126
<i>She even knew</i>
<i>the ledger was in the president's office.</i>

163
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,420
Hong Jang-mi, that crazy brat!

164
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:00,182
Jang-mi, how did you know…

165
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:03,436
I mean, Ms. Hong,
how did you know about the ledger?

166
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:06,731
Because President Kang
had offered it to me as evidence.

167
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,650
You knew my President Kang?

168
00:10:10,234 --> 00:10:11,235
Wait.

169
00:10:12,111 --> 00:10:15,448
But I thought he had that ledger
because he was managing the slush fund.

170
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:20,453
You call him <i>your</i> President Kang,
yet know nothing about him.

171
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:24,373
So you had no shame
about wanting to steal that money

172
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:27,001
because you thought
he was managing the slush fund?

173
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:27,918
Hey!

174
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,670
Anyone would think that.

175
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:32,548
Even though he showed me
nothing but respect and kindness,

176
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:34,258
he was still the son of a rich chairman.

177
00:10:34,342 --> 00:10:36,093
He and I came from different worlds.

178
00:10:36,177 --> 00:10:40,139
President Kang Myeong-hwi
wished to set Hanmin on the right path,

179
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:43,851
although he never even got a chance
to stand up to Chairman Kang.

180
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,689
We met a few times

181
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:50,232
to discuss the slush fund probe.

182
00:11:03,245 --> 00:11:04,580
Let's meet up

183
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:06,749
at our spot tonight.

184
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,043
All right.

185
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:16,592
Could it be

186
00:11:17,259 --> 00:11:20,137
that the woman he met
the night before his accident

187
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:23,474
was you, Hong Keum-bo?

188
00:11:23,557 --> 00:11:24,850
How do you know about that?

189
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,188
Ms. Song knows about it too.

190
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,650
Could she be suspecting you?

191
00:11:32,733 --> 00:11:35,111
She did ask me
for your personnel file back then.

192
00:11:35,194 --> 00:11:37,321
If she knew,
she would've done something by now.

193
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,239
Don't worry.

194
00:11:40,783 --> 00:11:41,951
Anyway,

195
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:44,161
I'm quitting
in the first week of December.

196
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:45,788
So let's just play dumb until then.

197
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:48,916
We'll part ways then and live our lives.

198
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:52,378
I'll treat you as Queen Bee
until my last day.

199
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:55,923
You're only saying that
because it'd hurt you if I dug any deeper.

200
00:11:57,216 --> 00:11:58,384
That's bold coming from you,

201
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,386
Ms. Go Bok-hee, the habitual embezzler.

202
00:12:01,595 --> 00:12:03,681
You should be grateful
I'm letting you off the hook.

203
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,391
I'm not an embezzler!

204
00:12:05,474 --> 00:12:08,936
Strictly speaking, I've never been
caught or arrested for such crimes.

205
00:12:09,019 --> 00:12:09,937
Why?

206
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:11,647
Because I only went after dirty money.

207
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:12,898
You must be so proud.

208
00:12:14,358 --> 00:12:16,068
Just leave right now.

209
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,486
I'm done worrying about you.

210
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:18,404
Jeez!

211
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:24,285
Either express concern or snap at me.

212
00:12:24,368 --> 00:12:25,744
Choose a lane, will you?

213
00:12:27,621 --> 00:12:29,123
CRIMINAL COMPLAINT

214
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:35,129
EPISODE 9: TWO LETTERS

215
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:47,641
Who is it?

216
00:12:49,226 --> 00:12:50,060
Who's there?

217
00:12:56,192 --> 00:12:58,194
Ms. Kim, why are you at my house?

218
00:12:58,777 --> 00:12:59,612
Sir.

219
00:13:02,781 --> 00:13:06,327
The New Korea Fund clients
filed criminal complaints against me.

220
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:08,037
You know what happened.

221
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:10,414
The head office promoted it
as their flagship product,

222
00:13:10,498 --> 00:13:13,709
and you kept pushing for us
to raise our sales figures as well.

223
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:14,835
Ms. Kim.

224
00:13:14,919 --> 00:13:15,961
Were you doing volunteer work?

225
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:18,923
Pardon?

226
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:21,592
The company can't help you
with personal lawsuits.

227
00:13:22,384 --> 00:13:23,511
Did you do it for the company's sake?

228
00:13:24,094 --> 00:13:25,638
You did it all for yourself,

229
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,139
so don't blame me now.

230
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:30,017
If you feel wronged,
you should pursue legal action.

231
00:13:30,809 --> 00:13:31,810
Sir.

232
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:33,479
Please help me.

233
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:35,356
Damn it, stop being such a pain!

234
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,234
Listen, Ms. Kim.

235
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:41,195
Consult a lawyer if you feel so wronged.

236
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:42,947
Damn it.

237
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:23,279
Welcome home, Auntie.

238
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:25,990
Bom, why are you out here alone?

239
00:14:26,073 --> 00:14:27,575
I'm waiting for Mommy.

240
00:14:31,912 --> 00:14:32,746
I see.

241
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,083
Should we page her?

242
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:37,418
Yes!

243
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:41,547
Let's see here.

244
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:48,387
<i>When you're done recording,</i>
<i>press the star or pound button…</i>

245
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:49,889
Press "8282."

246
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:52,141
8-2-8-2.

247
00:14:55,185 --> 00:14:56,395
We just told her to hurry home.

248
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:05,487
Once your mom gets home,
you have to go sleep in the room.

249
00:15:57,331 --> 00:15:59,166
Things must be hectic
at the branch right now.

250
00:15:59,249 --> 00:16:00,793
It must be tough on you as well.

251
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:09,969
I should've known better.

252
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:13,222
I put in all that effort for nothing.

253
00:17:34,094 --> 00:17:35,137
I'm going back to work.

254
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,098
I can't put this off anymore.

255
00:17:48,817 --> 00:17:49,818
See you.

256
00:18:10,923 --> 00:18:16,804
SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

257
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:39,868
<i>Even after securing</i>
<i>financial support from the IMF,</i>

258
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:42,454
<i>the foreign exchange crisis</i>
<i>shows no sign of easing.</i>

259
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:44,456
<i>As uncertainty over the outcome grows,</i>

260
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:47,251
{\an8}<i>the anxiety of the people</i>
<i>only continues to deepen.</i>

261
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:49,002
{\an8}HEONDAE INN

262
00:20:31,021 --> 00:20:36,652
{\an8}TO MS. HONG JANG-MI
TO CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM

263
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:47,621
<i>Please process my resignation</i>
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

264
00:20:53,585 --> 00:20:54,878
{\an8}LETTER OF RESIGNATION

265
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:06,098
EMERGENCY CONTACTS
MAGANG BRANCH: 3554-2988

266
00:21:10,894 --> 00:21:12,062
Is this the Magang Branch?

267
00:21:12,145 --> 00:21:15,524
I'm not a client,
but Ms. Kim Mi-sook's roommate.

268
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:19,528
She didn't show up to work today?

269
00:21:25,534 --> 00:21:26,493
Hello?

270
00:21:26,576 --> 00:21:27,786
<i>Is this Ms. Hong Jang-mi?</i>

271
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,621
<i>Do you know a Ms. Kim Mi-sook?</i>

272
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:32,040
Who's calling?

273
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:38,005
<i>Ms. Kim attempted to take her own life,</i>

274
00:21:38,088 --> 00:21:41,008
<i>and she left behind a suicide note</i>
<i>addressed to you at the scene.</i>

275
00:21:53,061 --> 00:21:55,605
<i>She left two suicide notes,</i>
<i>one addressed to you</i>

276
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:58,317
<i>and one addressed to</i>
<i>Chairman Kang of Hanmin.</i>

277
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:02,654
She left behind a letter
for Chairman Kang Pil-beom?

278
00:22:04,072 --> 00:22:05,073
What did it say?

279
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:07,659
It sounds like she felt wronged
by all the pressure at work.

280
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:10,370
Since the IMF crisis began,
a lot of laid-off workers

281
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:12,205
have fallen into such incidents.

282
00:22:12,289 --> 00:22:14,499
Since the investigation is still ongoing,

283
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:16,793
we had to review the contents
of the suicide notes.

284
00:22:37,522 --> 00:22:39,399
TO MS. HONG JANG-MI

285
00:22:50,952 --> 00:22:54,247
<i>I thought long and hard about</i>
<i>who to ask for such a difficult favor,</i>

286
00:22:54,915 --> 00:22:57,793
<i>and the only person</i>
<i>I could think of was you, Jang-mi.</i>

287
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:01,463
{\an8}<i>Nine years ago,</i>

288
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:04,883
{\an8}<i>when I was still a high school senior,</i>
<i>I started my first job</i>

289
00:23:04,966 --> 00:23:06,927
<i>at Cheongsan Accounting Firm.</i>

290
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:08,095
Ms. Kim, get us some coffee.

291
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:09,721
Yes, sir.

292
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:11,681
<i>I was thrilled to work</i>
<i>at such a big company,</i>

293
00:23:11,765 --> 00:23:13,558
<i>but I felt</i>
<i>just as much pressure to do well.</i>

294
00:23:14,142 --> 00:23:16,061
<i>I found myself constantly on edge at work.</i>

295
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:18,063
<i>One day, those nerves got so bad</i>

296
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:20,315
<i>that I spilled coffee</i>
<i>on an accountant's documents.</i>

297
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:21,233
I'm so sorry!

298
00:23:32,369 --> 00:23:33,995
I'm terribly sorry.

299
00:23:34,079 --> 00:23:35,205
You should apologize

300
00:23:35,288 --> 00:23:37,541
for interrupting my work,
not for spilling coffee.

301
00:23:37,624 --> 00:23:39,793
<i>I wonder if you remember telling me that.</i>

302
00:23:40,293 --> 00:23:42,087
Way to call her out.

303
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:43,922
You can go.

304
00:23:50,971 --> 00:23:54,015
<i>To this day, I vividly remember</i>
<i>how you told off my boss,</i>

305
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:57,060
<i>who was harassing me</i>
<i>in the emergency stairwell.</i>

306
00:23:57,561 --> 00:23:59,688
Sir, why did you ask to see me?

307
00:23:59,771 --> 00:24:02,190
You're free this weekend, right?

308
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:06,486
Sir, as I told you last time,

309
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:08,446
I'm not looking to date anyone
at the moment.

310
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:11,366
Hey.

311
00:24:11,867 --> 00:24:14,953
Being young is nothing special.
Stop playing hard to get already.

312
00:24:15,036 --> 00:24:19,166
Besides, I know you're just working here
to snag yourself a decent man.

313
00:24:19,749 --> 00:24:22,252
- That's not true.
- Don't lie to me. Listen, Ms. Kim--

314
00:24:22,335 --> 00:24:24,796
- Please don't do this.
- It's just dinner.

315
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:25,881
Let me treat you to--

316
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:28,258
What the…

317
00:24:29,634 --> 00:24:30,635
What the hell?

318
00:24:30,719 --> 00:24:32,345
Come on now, you know me.

319
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:34,181
I'm Hong Keum-bo,
the one who calls people out.

320
00:24:35,765 --> 00:24:38,018
Are you crazy?
Is that any way to treat your senior?

321
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:40,187
If you're a senior, act your damn age.

322
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:41,938
You just sent out
your wedding invitations.

323
00:24:42,022 --> 00:24:44,858
No decent human being would hit on
a high school girl 12 years his junior.

324
00:24:45,734 --> 00:24:47,777
If you ever bother her again,

325
00:24:47,861 --> 00:24:50,780
I will do everything in my power
to end you…

326
00:24:52,073 --> 00:24:54,784
both physically and socially.

327
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:57,370
I can't believe this. Damn it.

328
00:24:59,247 --> 00:25:00,290
Are you okay?

329
00:25:03,919 --> 00:25:04,836
Why are you crying?

330
00:25:05,629 --> 00:25:07,255
Because I'm so embarrassed.

331
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:26,441
She reported Hanmin for accounting fraud,

332
00:25:26,942 --> 00:25:29,277
but their countersuit ruined her.

333
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:31,696
- How naive.
- Seriously.

334
00:25:33,448 --> 00:25:34,908
Wait, my wallet.

335
00:25:37,661 --> 00:25:39,704
I left my wallet in the office.

336
00:25:41,706 --> 00:25:44,251
It's past 2 p.m., so you
no longer have access to the office.

337
00:25:44,334 --> 00:25:45,502
Please follow the company rules.

338
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:49,965
You can't ask me to follow the rules
when I don't even work here anymore.

339
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:50,966
You can't go back.

340
00:25:51,883 --> 00:25:53,009
I said you can't!

341
00:26:03,478 --> 00:26:04,896
<i>Nine years have passed,</i>

342
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:07,524
<i>but I never stopped looking up to you.</i>

343
00:26:07,607 --> 00:26:09,734
You left your wallet behind.

344
00:26:12,404 --> 00:26:13,280
Thank you.

345
00:26:15,282 --> 00:26:17,284
<i>I couldn't be of any help to you</i>

346
00:26:17,367 --> 00:26:19,703
<i>when you were</i>
<i>wrongfully forced to leave the company.</i>

347
00:26:19,786 --> 00:26:21,329
<i>But this time,</i>

348
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:23,248
<i>I was determined to protect you.</i>

349
00:26:24,916 --> 00:26:25,750
Hello.

350
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:27,794
Room 301?

351
00:26:28,628 --> 00:26:30,297
- Hello.
- Hi.

352
00:26:32,632 --> 00:26:33,758
I'm Room 301 too.

353
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:36,219
<i>On the day we moved into the dorms,</i>

354
00:26:36,303 --> 00:26:38,221
<i>you had a different name,</i>

355
00:26:38,305 --> 00:26:40,682
<i>but I still recognized you.</i>

356
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:44,227
<i>I was sure you had your reasons.</i>

357
00:26:44,978 --> 00:26:46,730
<i>I didn't want to interfere.</i>

358
00:26:48,273 --> 00:26:51,026
Bom, do you enjoy
living with the aunties and me?

359
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:52,402
Yes, I do!

360
00:26:54,654 --> 00:26:57,490
Bom, who's your favorite auntie?

361
00:26:58,491 --> 00:26:59,617
Auntie Jang-mi.

362
00:27:05,165 --> 00:27:07,375
I like that auntie too.

363
00:27:10,211 --> 00:27:14,049
<i>Thank you for welcoming Bom into your life</i>
<i>and taking such good care of her.</i>

364
00:27:15,216 --> 00:27:16,634
<i>One morning,</i>

365
00:27:16,718 --> 00:27:20,472
<i>Bom showed off the dollhouse</i>
<i>she made with you.</i>

366
00:27:21,097 --> 00:27:23,850
<i>She held up five fingers</i>
<i>and proudly said to me,</i>

367
00:27:25,101 --> 00:27:27,729
<i>"We are a family of five."</i>

368
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:34,611
<i>I worked hard because I wanted to find</i>
<i>a place for Bom and me.</i>

369
00:27:35,111 --> 00:27:37,739
<i>I can't burden her with my debt.</i>

370
00:27:39,532 --> 00:27:40,784
<i>After I'm gone,</i>

371
00:27:41,368 --> 00:27:43,995
<i>please help her renounce her inheritance.</i>

372
00:27:45,580 --> 00:27:49,709
<i>And please tell her</i>
<i>that her mommy loves her very much.</i>

373
00:27:52,670 --> 00:27:55,590
<i>I hope the letter I wrote to the chairman</i>
<i>finds its way to him,</i>

374
00:27:55,673 --> 00:27:58,927
<i>and that he's able to rectify</i>
<i>the situation with the clients.</i>

375
00:28:02,347 --> 00:28:05,517
<i>Please forgive me</i>
<i>for making such difficult requests.</i>

376
00:28:06,309 --> 00:28:07,852
<i>But still,</i>

377
00:28:08,436 --> 00:28:10,063
<i>I'm glad I got to meet you again,</i>

378
00:28:10,146 --> 00:28:11,106
<i>Keum-bo.</i>

379
00:28:25,161 --> 00:28:26,538
Mi-sook.

380
00:28:27,747 --> 00:28:29,165
She's still unconscious.

381
00:28:30,542 --> 00:28:31,918
Mi-sook…

382
00:28:34,254 --> 00:28:36,339
She's still unconscious. Leave her alone!

383
00:28:37,006 --> 00:28:39,134
Why are you yelling at me?

384
00:28:41,344 --> 00:28:42,512
Why am I yelling at you?

385
00:28:42,595 --> 00:28:44,264
Mi-sook sold those funds

386
00:28:44,347 --> 00:28:46,599
because the head office
pressured her for sales, no?

387
00:28:48,101 --> 00:28:49,310
Excuse me.

388
00:28:49,894 --> 00:28:51,104
Can you three keep it down?

389
00:28:52,105 --> 00:28:53,022
Sorry.

390
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:55,900
That has nothing to do with Eun-joo.

391
00:28:56,526 --> 00:28:58,027
It most certainly does.

392
00:28:58,111 --> 00:28:59,612
You tell her, Kang Nora.

393
00:29:05,660 --> 00:29:06,619
Kang Nora?

394
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:09,372
You knew, Queen Bee?

395
00:29:09,456 --> 00:29:10,832
Of course I did.

396
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:14,043
I only catered to you
because of your lofty title.

397
00:29:14,127 --> 00:29:16,713
Mi-sook ended up like this
because of your father's orders,

398
00:29:16,796 --> 00:29:18,298
yet you think you're blameless?

399
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:24,637
Hold on.

400
00:29:24,721 --> 00:29:26,389
You're Chairman Kang Pil-beom's
only daughter,

401
00:29:26,473 --> 00:29:27,682
Kang Nora?

402
00:29:29,476 --> 00:29:31,352
The three of you need to leave.

403
00:29:32,270 --> 00:29:33,104
Come on.

404
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:39,903
Are you really Kang Nora?

405
00:29:40,862 --> 00:29:42,363
But I wasn't trying to hide it.

406
00:29:42,447 --> 00:29:44,199
You never asked who my dad was.

407
00:29:44,282 --> 00:29:46,159
Why are you in the company and the dorms?

408
00:29:46,242 --> 00:29:48,578
My dad said if I survived
the probationary period,

409
00:29:48,661 --> 00:29:50,789
I could have my brother's company shares.

410
00:29:52,373 --> 00:29:53,208
His shares?

411
00:29:53,291 --> 00:29:56,252
But Eun-joo really is my name,
from when I was younger.

412
00:29:56,336 --> 00:29:58,254
Don't get mad, Jang-mi.

413
00:29:58,338 --> 00:30:00,256
She's ten whole years older than you.

414
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:02,592
She's even older than me. She's 35!

415
00:30:03,426 --> 00:30:04,886
Hey, why bring that up now?

416
00:30:04,969 --> 00:30:06,179
Oh my god.

417
00:30:06,262 --> 00:30:08,348
Hong Jang-mi, you're 35?

418
00:30:08,431 --> 00:30:09,849
She's not Hong Jang-mi, she's Hong…

419
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:12,811
Sis, you should just come clean now too.

420
00:30:12,894 --> 00:30:14,187
About what?

421
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:15,730
And why are you calling me that?

422
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:18,441
I don't recall ever having
an embezzler as a younger sister.

423
00:30:18,525 --> 00:30:20,026
"Embezzler"?

424
00:30:20,109 --> 00:30:21,694
I told you I'm not an embezzler!

425
00:30:21,778 --> 00:30:24,447
What about you?
Are you proud of lying your way in?

426
00:30:24,531 --> 00:30:27,575
If you think about it,
you're the biggest liar here.

427
00:30:27,659 --> 00:30:29,536
Your name, age, job, and even education!

428
00:30:30,245 --> 00:30:32,539
I saw your graduation photo
at your parents' restaurant,

429
00:30:32,622 --> 00:30:33,748
proudly hanging on the wall.

430
00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:35,625
When I told you

431
00:30:36,167 --> 00:30:38,878
that it wasn't too late
for you to go to college,

432
00:30:39,504 --> 00:30:42,340
how pathetic I must've seemed
while you laughed at me inside!

433
00:30:42,423 --> 00:30:43,550
I did not.

434
00:30:47,303 --> 00:30:48,137
For now,

435
00:30:49,222 --> 00:30:51,099
you two should go back
and take care of Bom.

436
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:54,352
I'll stay with Mi-sook tonight.

437
00:31:07,198 --> 00:31:09,033
DISCUSSION BOARD

438
00:31:09,117 --> 00:31:11,327
