440
00:31:12,537 --> 00:31:14,080
AFTER CRIMINAL COMPLAINTS WERE FILED…

441
00:31:14,163 --> 00:31:15,915
VIEW COUNT

442
00:31:15,999 --> 00:31:17,709
HANMIN MAGANG BRANCH
FEMALE EMPLOYEE K ATTEMPTS SUICIDE

443
00:31:17,792 --> 00:31:19,002
2 SUICIDE NOTES FOUND

444
00:31:20,753 --> 00:31:22,338
{\an8}HANMIN MAGANG BRANCH
FEMALE EMPLOYEE K ATTEMPTS SUICIDE

445
00:31:22,422 --> 00:31:23,965
Damn it!

446
00:31:25,049 --> 00:31:26,426
A suicide attempt?

447
00:31:27,135 --> 00:31:31,306
The article seems to have been written
by a police-beat reporter

448
00:31:31,389 --> 00:31:34,017
who managed to overhear
details of the case at the station.

449
00:31:34,100 --> 00:31:36,019
Must we allow Hanmin

450
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:38,897
to be mentioned
in such a disgraceful manner?

451
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:40,440
What's this suicide note about?

452
00:31:40,523 --> 00:31:44,193
She left one addressed to you, sir,

453
00:31:44,277 --> 00:31:47,947
and one addressed to Hong Jang-mi,
her dormitory roommate.

454
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:51,659
The officer in charge of the investigation

455
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:52,952
delivered this yesterday.

456
00:31:53,786 --> 00:31:54,871
Let's see.

457
00:32:04,213 --> 00:32:07,550
<i>I am Kim Mi-sook,</i>
<i>an employee at Hanmin's Magang Branch.</i>

458
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:11,554
<i>The head office sent a directive</i>
<i>that raised the sales targets,</i>

459
00:32:12,138 --> 00:32:14,432
<i>and the branch</i>
<i>reported our sales every week.</i>

460
00:32:15,016 --> 00:32:16,935
<i>Everyone including myself at the branch</i>

461
00:32:17,018 --> 00:32:20,438
<i>worked hard to meet the sales target</i>
<i>set by the head office.</i>

462
00:32:21,856 --> 00:32:23,983
<i>So why is it</i>
<i>that only the branch employees</i>

463
00:32:24,067 --> 00:32:26,277
<i>must bear the backlash from the clients?</i>

464
00:32:27,278 --> 00:32:28,112
<i>Sir.</i>

465
00:32:28,696 --> 00:32:30,573
<i>- Your employees deserve better.</i>
- "Your employees

466
00:32:30,657 --> 00:32:33,701
deserve better."

467
00:32:34,953 --> 00:32:38,748
"I hope the company takes the initiative

468
00:32:38,831 --> 00:32:41,709
to resolve this matter."

469
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:44,504
Goddamn it.

470
00:32:51,344 --> 00:32:54,263
That extreme decision was hers alone.

471
00:32:55,056 --> 00:32:56,933
It has nothing to do with the company.

472
00:32:58,184 --> 00:33:01,646
Mr. Oh, take care of the press.

473
00:33:01,729 --> 00:33:03,022
Yes, sir.

474
00:33:03,106 --> 00:33:04,524
I want you to make sure

475
00:33:04,607 --> 00:33:07,360
they don't bring up our company
or the New Korea Fund.

476
00:33:08,027 --> 00:33:10,697
And make it clear
that if they keep writing such articles,

477
00:33:10,780 --> 00:33:14,075
they can forget about us
buying any more ad space.

478
00:33:14,158 --> 00:33:16,202
Yes, sir. I'll take care of it.

479
00:33:16,828 --> 00:33:19,080
Also, Ms. Song,

480
00:33:19,163 --> 00:33:22,917
instruct the branch managers
to shred all related official documents.

481
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:25,795
And this roommate
she left that other suicide note for,

482
00:33:25,878 --> 00:33:29,173
make sure
she keeps her mouth shut as well.

483
00:33:29,674 --> 00:33:32,385
We must avoid
setting a dangerous precedent.

484
00:33:32,969 --> 00:33:34,971
If we console them out of pity,

485
00:33:35,722 --> 00:33:38,141
they'll only cling on and drag us down.

486
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:40,184
Yes, sir.

487
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:44,605
Besides, we must ensure
that our future partner,

488
00:33:45,148 --> 00:33:47,316
DK Ventures,

489
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:49,902
forms a positive first impression of us.

490
00:33:50,611 --> 00:33:53,489
We can't let such unpleasant news
be our introduction.

491
00:33:54,073 --> 00:33:55,658
Don't you agree, President Shin?

492
00:33:56,284 --> 00:33:58,870
I don't anticipate any substantial impact.

493
00:33:58,953 --> 00:34:00,038
All right then.

494
00:34:01,914 --> 00:34:03,624
My goodness.

495
00:34:10,423 --> 00:34:13,926
I saw on Yeouido Pirates
that Ms. K from Magang Branch

496
00:34:14,010 --> 00:34:15,845
even left a suicide note
for her roommates.

497
00:34:17,263 --> 00:34:18,514
Have you heard anything from Ms. Hong?

498
00:34:18,598 --> 00:34:19,766
I haven't.

499
00:34:19,849 --> 00:34:20,725
I haven't either.

500
00:34:22,643 --> 00:34:23,686
Why not?

501
00:34:25,396 --> 00:34:26,439
How about this?

502
00:34:26,522 --> 00:34:28,441
I'll call her to a conference room
and ask her.

503
00:34:28,524 --> 00:34:31,110
- She came to work today.
- You're just asking for a beating.

504
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:32,904
I'll bet 10,000 won on a face slap.

505
00:34:32,987 --> 00:34:35,615
She might use a fist, not an open hand.

506
00:34:35,698 --> 00:34:37,241
- A mighty punch.
- Why you…

507
00:34:38,367 --> 00:34:41,245
I mean, you're all curious, aren't you?

508
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:43,831
You're a general manager, so act like one.

509
00:34:44,624 --> 00:34:47,126
Did you hear anything
about how the company will respond?

510
00:34:47,210 --> 00:34:49,545
I'm sure they'll clamp down on all fronts.

511
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:50,505
Quietly, that is.

512
00:35:00,223 --> 00:35:01,057
Hong Jang-mi.

513
00:35:01,766 --> 00:35:03,559
Are you going to see Ms. Song too?

514
00:35:04,811 --> 00:35:06,395
I'm sure it'll be about Mi-sook.

515
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:13,486
I hear you're roommates
with Ms. Kim Mi-sook.

516
00:35:15,488 --> 00:35:16,614
Yes, that's right.

517
00:35:17,824 --> 00:35:19,867
Did you write that post
on Yeouido Pirates, Ms. Go?

518
00:35:20,785 --> 00:35:21,619
No, ma'am.

519
00:35:21,702 --> 00:35:23,579
I would never, ma'am.

520
00:35:25,331 --> 00:35:26,290
Was it you, Ms. Hong?

521
00:35:29,335 --> 00:35:30,628
It wasn't you.

522
00:35:30,711 --> 00:35:33,297
Did you call us in
to find out who leaked it?

523
00:35:34,423 --> 00:35:36,008
Kim Mi-sook is an orphan.

524
00:35:36,092 --> 00:35:39,846
If anyone were to leak it,
it would be the suicide note recipient

525
00:35:40,555 --> 00:35:42,974
or her roommate in the dorms.

526
00:35:43,891 --> 00:35:46,561
Hong Jang-mi,
she wrote you a note, didn't she?

527
00:35:48,062 --> 00:35:49,605
Ms. Kim Mi-sook's suicide attempt

528
00:35:49,689 --> 00:35:52,150
is undeniably the result
of work-related stress.

529
00:35:53,025 --> 00:35:55,486
Shouldn't you ask about
how she's doing first?

530
00:35:56,445 --> 00:35:58,281
How can the head office, the branch,

531
00:35:58,364 --> 00:36:00,908
and even the OW Club
that the victim admired,

532
00:36:00,992 --> 00:36:03,494
all just erase her
and pretend as if nothing happened

533
00:36:03,995 --> 00:36:05,705
to prioritize damage control?

534
00:36:06,330 --> 00:36:07,748
If, in any case, she'd died--

535
00:36:07,832 --> 00:36:09,125
But she didn't die.

536
00:36:11,419 --> 00:36:13,296
What's with this fuss
when she's still alive?

537
00:36:16,591 --> 00:36:18,217
Just hand over the suicide note.

538
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:33,149
Those are the criminal complaints
filed against Hanmin's Ms. Kim Mi-sook

539
00:36:33,232 --> 00:36:36,777
that demand compensatory damages
for the New Korea Funds she sold.

540
00:36:37,653 --> 00:36:39,655
Will the company deal with the lawsuits?

541
00:36:39,739 --> 00:36:41,824
Otherwise, at least help
with her hospital bills.

542
00:36:43,784 --> 00:36:45,369
You have some nerve.

543
00:36:45,453 --> 00:36:48,372
Let me apologize on her behalf, ma'am.
I'll have a talk with her.

544
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:50,249
She's just in a state of shock right now.

545
00:36:58,007 --> 00:36:59,926
{\an8}HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

546
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,694
Hey, Ms. Hong.

547
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:22,949
You're roommates with Kim Mi-sook
from the Magang Branch, right?

548
00:37:23,908 --> 00:37:24,742
Yes.

549
00:37:24,825 --> 00:37:25,660
Come on.

550
00:37:26,535 --> 00:37:27,787
I heard she left

551
00:37:28,454 --> 00:37:30,206
a suicide note for the roommates.

552
00:37:30,289 --> 00:37:32,291
Did you read it? What did it say?

553
00:37:32,917 --> 00:37:36,337
I heard she addressed the complaints
about the company to the chairman.

554
00:37:37,588 --> 00:37:39,423
She must've written
something else to her friends.

555
00:37:39,507 --> 00:37:40,967
What's it to you?

556
00:37:41,050 --> 00:37:42,343
I'm just curious.

557
00:37:44,553 --> 00:37:47,223
- Let us in on the gossip.
- Mr. Cha.

558
00:37:47,306 --> 00:37:49,350
What's wrong with you?

559
00:37:49,433 --> 00:37:50,726
If the job was killing her,

560
00:37:51,394 --> 00:37:52,687
she could've just quit.

561
00:37:52,770 --> 00:37:54,563
Why attempt suicide?

562
00:37:58,109 --> 00:37:59,110
Asshole!

563
00:38:07,952 --> 00:38:09,287
What? "Asshole"?

564
00:38:09,370 --> 00:38:10,288
Come here.

565
00:38:10,997 --> 00:38:12,373
I can't believe this.

566
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:16,377
There's big trouble. Come out now!

567
00:38:18,087 --> 00:38:19,255
What did you say?

568
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:21,632
Unbelievable.

569
00:38:22,883 --> 00:38:24,468
- "Asshole"?
- Yes! Asshole!

570
00:38:26,345 --> 00:38:27,888
Do I look like a peer to you?

571
00:38:29,015 --> 00:38:31,142
If we were peers,
you wouldn't be standing.

572
00:38:31,225 --> 00:38:32,977
You'd already be crushed under my feet!

573
00:38:33,060 --> 00:38:34,645
Goddamn.

574
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:38,024
Can you believe this?

575
00:38:38,899 --> 00:38:40,067
Listen.

576
00:38:40,151 --> 00:38:41,319
You and I?

577
00:38:42,278 --> 00:38:44,405
When it comes to rank, age, and gender,

578
00:38:44,488 --> 00:38:47,158
you're nowhere near my level
in any respect!

579
00:38:48,659 --> 00:38:51,162
Why you little… You damn brat!

580
00:38:59,295 --> 00:39:00,254
Asshole.

581
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:01,255
What?

582
00:39:01,339 --> 00:39:02,840
When someone younger criticizes you,

583
00:39:02,923 --> 00:39:06,677
that should be a sign to reflect
on the poor choices you've made.

584
00:39:08,596 --> 00:39:09,930
Ms. Hong, please try to calm down.

585
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:11,599
Don't touch me!

586
00:39:14,810 --> 00:39:17,480
If you ever run that mouth
about Mi-sook again,

587
00:39:19,357 --> 00:39:20,649
I will end you.

588
00:39:22,735 --> 00:39:23,986
Damn it.

589
00:39:25,988 --> 00:39:27,990
Damn it. Come here.

590
00:39:28,074 --> 00:39:29,450
Hey, Hong Jang-mi!

591
00:39:30,743 --> 00:39:32,286
- Why that little…
- Unbelievable.

592
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:33,245
Ms. Hong!

593
00:39:35,581 --> 00:39:36,582
Go.

594
00:39:38,125 --> 00:39:38,959
Hey!

595
00:39:40,628 --> 00:39:42,213
Hong Jang-mi!

596
00:39:42,296 --> 00:39:43,881
Your days are numbered here!

597
00:39:43,964 --> 00:39:45,007
Stop it.

598
00:39:45,091 --> 00:39:46,550
I'll make sure of it!

599
00:39:49,470 --> 00:39:51,722
- You're so loud.
- You went too far.

600
00:39:52,223 --> 00:39:54,266
What are you staring at? Damn it.

601
00:39:55,142 --> 00:39:56,435
It hurts.

602
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:57,353
Get back to work!

603
00:39:57,436 --> 00:40:00,106
He's so goddamn embarrassing.

604
00:40:00,856 --> 00:40:02,149
Where did Mr. So go?

605
00:40:02,233 --> 00:40:04,276
He's probably upset
because he's menopausal.

606
00:40:08,531 --> 00:40:09,573
It's okay.

607
00:40:09,657 --> 00:40:11,784
Take the next three days off,
starting today.

608
00:40:14,328 --> 00:40:15,413
You'll leave immediately.

609
00:40:17,957 --> 00:40:19,041
I apologize for causing…

610
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:21,502
such a commotion.

611
00:40:22,503 --> 00:40:23,462
Thank you…

612
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:25,714
for holding back.

613
00:40:29,385 --> 00:40:31,137
If you had actually hit him…

614
00:40:32,221 --> 00:40:33,347
Right, you did.

615
00:40:34,098 --> 00:40:35,766
It's okay. I'll take care of it.

616
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:39,437
I might not look it,
but I'm still a division manager.

617
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:46,527
{\an8}LETTER OF RESIGNATION

618
00:40:48,070 --> 00:40:49,405
It's my resignation letter.

619
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:07,465
Why are you following me?
Go and look after Bom.

620
00:41:08,007 --> 00:41:09,175
I have something to ask you.

621
00:41:09,258 --> 00:41:11,969
When did you find out that I was Nora?

622
00:41:12,052 --> 00:41:13,512
Since you joined the company.

623
00:41:13,596 --> 00:41:16,056
Ms. Song ordered me to monitor you.

624
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:17,266
Ms. Song did?

625
00:41:18,017 --> 00:41:19,894
And you agreed to do it, Queen Bee?

626
00:41:20,895 --> 00:41:21,896
It was an order.

627
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:24,648
Besides, why am I still "Queen Bee"?

628
00:41:24,732 --> 00:41:25,733
Hong Jang-mi…

629
00:41:25,816 --> 00:41:27,026
No, Hong Keum…

630
00:41:27,610 --> 00:41:29,653
Whatever her name is, she's Queen Bee now.

631
00:41:30,279 --> 00:41:31,155
Nora.

632
00:41:43,250 --> 00:41:44,543
Ms. Go, right?

633
00:41:45,753 --> 00:41:47,671
I've heard a lot about you from Ms. Song.

634
00:41:47,755 --> 00:41:49,256
Yes, ma'am.

635
00:41:50,299 --> 00:41:51,759
Nora, let's go home now.

636
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:53,594
Home?

637
00:41:53,677 --> 00:41:54,720
But this is my home.

638
00:41:54,803 --> 00:41:56,013
What are you talking about?

639
00:41:56,096 --> 00:41:57,932
I told you earlier.

640
00:41:58,015 --> 00:41:59,350
You're moving into Dad's place.

641
00:41:59,934 --> 00:42:01,477
I can't today.

642
00:42:03,062 --> 00:42:05,773
Someone is waiting for me inside.

643
00:42:05,856 --> 00:42:08,984
We can have the housekeeper come by
to pick up your stuff.

644
00:42:09,485 --> 00:42:10,694
Wait, no.

645
00:42:10,778 --> 00:42:12,947
You can pack Nora's stuff
and send it over, right?

646
00:42:14,740 --> 00:42:16,158
Sure, ma'am.

647
00:42:16,825 --> 00:42:17,910
Thank you.

648
00:42:17,993 --> 00:42:18,994
Let's go.

649
00:42:19,537 --> 00:42:21,080
It's so cold today.

650
00:42:24,959 --> 00:42:25,793
Go on.

651
00:42:34,843 --> 00:42:35,761
Damn it.

652
00:42:46,730 --> 00:42:48,232
Why does she have so many clothes?

653
00:42:54,321 --> 00:42:56,240
Those are Auntie Eun-joo's.

654
00:42:56,991 --> 00:42:59,535
She went home. She's not coming back.

655
00:42:59,618 --> 00:43:01,036
Then,

656
00:43:01,537 --> 00:43:04,081
did Auntie Jang-mi go home too?

657
00:43:07,459 --> 00:43:08,335
No.

658
00:43:08,419 --> 00:43:10,379
She's with your mom.

659
00:43:19,179 --> 00:43:22,266
Starting tonight,
you can sleep with me in the big room.

660
00:43:25,603 --> 00:43:28,188
Where's Mommy?

661
00:43:57,760 --> 00:43:58,886
Bom.

662
00:44:17,237 --> 00:44:18,822
Why did you bring her here?

663
00:44:18,906 --> 00:44:20,115
What did you tell her?

664
00:44:20,199 --> 00:44:21,533
I told her it was an accident.

665
00:44:22,076 --> 00:44:24,370
She deserves to know where her mom is.

666
00:44:25,371 --> 00:44:28,332
We can't just leave her alone
in the dorms for the night.

667
00:44:29,041 --> 00:44:30,542
Why would she be alone? Where's Nora?

668
00:44:30,626 --> 00:44:32,336
She left with her mom earlier.

669
00:44:32,419 --> 00:44:34,338
She left for good.

670
00:44:37,549 --> 00:44:39,009
I've thought about it all day.

671
00:44:39,927 --> 00:44:42,471
Let me see the rest of Mi-sook's letter.

672
00:44:42,554 --> 00:44:43,889
I need to read it for myself.

673
00:45:29,101 --> 00:45:32,146
Have you ever prayed for someone
other than yourself?

674
00:45:34,398 --> 00:45:37,151
I didn't recognize her when we met again,

675
00:45:38,861 --> 00:45:41,947
and I'm still not sure
I know what kind of person Mi-sook is.

676
00:45:45,993 --> 00:45:46,827
But…

677
00:45:49,997 --> 00:45:50,998
I do remember…

678
00:45:53,750 --> 00:45:56,962
that she prayed for me, for us.

679
00:45:58,338 --> 00:46:00,716
Why couldn't she just think about herself?

680
00:46:05,888 --> 00:46:06,763
If…

681
00:46:09,099 --> 00:46:10,726
If I had told her

682
00:46:12,144 --> 00:46:14,354
that it wasn't her fault that night,

683
00:46:15,814 --> 00:46:17,357
would she have been okay now?

684
00:46:22,279 --> 00:46:24,448
You thought you got away with it
because you were clever, huh?

685
00:46:25,282 --> 00:46:26,492
We let you get away with it.

686
00:46:27,117 --> 00:46:28,911
I let you get away with it,
and so did Mi-sook.

687
00:46:30,496 --> 00:46:33,123
I let you because I felt bad
that Go Bok-cheol attacked you,

688
00:46:34,458 --> 00:46:37,377
but Mi-sook let you because
she's just too nice for her own good!

689
00:46:39,630 --> 00:46:41,632
Poor Mi-sook…

690
00:46:52,434 --> 00:46:53,268
Bom.

691
00:46:57,064 --> 00:46:57,898
Bom…

692
00:46:59,816 --> 00:47:01,401
What are we going to do?

693
00:47:06,823 --> 00:47:07,658
Bom…

694
00:47:13,872 --> 00:47:17,084
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

695
00:47:20,337 --> 00:47:21,255
Hey.

696
00:47:25,008 --> 00:47:26,134
Thank you for making the trip.

697
00:47:26,218 --> 00:47:27,469
I'm exhausted.

698
00:47:27,553 --> 00:47:29,638
Did you enjoy the meal we prepared?

699
00:47:29,721 --> 00:47:31,557
- It was delicious.
- I'm glad.

700
00:47:31,640 --> 00:47:33,475
Nice to meet you. I'm Oh Deok-gyu.

701
00:47:33,559 --> 00:47:35,686
- Yes, hello. I'm--
- Let's talk inside.

702
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:37,437
Sure.

703
00:47:43,819 --> 00:47:45,237
{\an8}It's a pleasure to meet you.

704
00:47:45,320 --> 00:47:47,406
I'm D.K. Lee of DK Ventures.

705
00:47:48,657 --> 00:47:50,492
I am Kang Pil-beom.

706
00:47:52,786 --> 00:47:54,580
Please take a seat.

707
00:47:55,664 --> 00:47:56,748
Let's sit.

708
00:47:59,751 --> 00:48:02,963
Should we get right to it then?

709
00:48:03,046 --> 00:48:04,006
Sir.

710
00:48:04,089 --> 00:48:07,384
DK Ventures wishes to dispatch
an investment due diligence team here

711
00:48:07,467 --> 00:48:09,845
to the head office next week.

712
00:48:10,345 --> 00:48:12,389
Before that,
I'd like to sort out a few things first.

713
00:48:13,515 --> 00:48:17,311
We heard Hanmin is in urgent need of
300 billion won in operating funds.

714
00:48:17,894 --> 00:48:21,815
Based on the financial statements,
some members of our board are concerned

715
00:48:22,649 --> 00:48:24,401
about Hanmin's management soundness.

716
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:28,196
So we'd like management control
along with a portion of the equity.

717
00:48:30,365 --> 00:48:32,367
Management control as well?

718
00:48:33,535 --> 00:48:34,911
It'll benefit both parties.

719
00:48:34,995 --> 00:48:36,246
That's not what worries me.

720
00:48:36,330 --> 00:48:39,458
My concern is that you'll be asking
for the whole company next.

721
00:48:40,667 --> 00:48:45,005
How about using
the head office building as collateral?

722
00:48:45,088 --> 00:48:48,675
Our company does hold
a considerable amount of real estate,

723
00:48:48,759 --> 00:48:50,218
both in land and buildings.

724
00:48:50,719 --> 00:48:52,638
Having a mortgage against our real estate

725
00:48:53,472 --> 00:48:55,557
could negatively affect
the company's public image.

726
00:49:02,356 --> 00:49:04,650
My goodness…

727
00:49:07,069 --> 00:49:12,157
What if Hanmin issues bonds
that DK Ventures could purchase directly?

728
00:49:14,284 --> 00:49:15,786
If public funds are reinjected,

729
00:49:15,869 --> 00:49:17,704
maintaining a domestically owned image

730
00:49:17,788 --> 00:49:20,666
while avoiding the appearance
of overseas backing

731
00:49:20,749 --> 00:49:22,334
could work in our favor.

732
00:49:26,421 --> 00:49:28,340
Would you consider that?

733
00:49:28,423 --> 00:49:31,468
I believe DK Ventures' payout

734
00:49:32,052 --> 00:49:34,513
would certainly be ensured with that idea.

735
00:49:36,181 --> 00:49:37,349
Okay.

736
00:49:37,432 --> 00:49:38,558
It's not a bad deal.

737
00:49:39,643 --> 00:49:40,769
And one more thing.

738
00:49:40,852 --> 00:49:44,314
An organization must be lightweight
for efficient management,

739
00:49:45,023 --> 00:49:48,735
but Hanmin is weighed down
by too much dead weight at the moment.

740
00:49:51,446 --> 00:49:54,116
We'd like to request
aggressive cuts in labor costs.

741
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:56,076
You know,

742
00:49:56,827 --> 00:49:57,744
a diet.

743
00:50:00,872 --> 00:50:04,042
Cutting costs
will help balance our profit and loss.

744
00:50:06,002 --> 00:50:08,004
Yes. I understand.

745
00:50:09,172 --> 00:50:12,759
After all, a good presentation
goes a long way.

746
00:50:17,139 --> 00:50:18,849
I knew Chairman Kang would say that.

747
00:50:19,391 --> 00:50:21,143
He's stingy with his own,

748
00:50:21,727 --> 00:50:24,062
but happy to rack up debt
with other people's money.

749
00:50:25,605 --> 00:50:28,692
He'll issue short-term bonds
with a one-year maturity,

750
00:50:28,775 --> 00:50:31,403
then ask to extend the repayment period
by another year or two.

751
00:50:31,987 --> 00:50:35,031
In the meantime,
we'll quietly accumulate more bonds.

752
00:50:35,615 --> 00:50:37,784
And if Hanmin goes bankrupt on its own?
That's a win for us.

753
00:50:38,702 --> 00:50:39,536
<i>What if,</i>

754
00:50:40,662 --> 00:50:42,038
in the worst-case scenario,

755
00:50:42,873 --> 00:50:45,125
Hanmin Investment & Securities
goes bankrupt?

756
00:50:45,208 --> 00:50:47,085
We can file
for a court-mediated debt workout

757
00:50:47,169 --> 00:50:49,421
and request an extension
of the repayment period.

758
00:50:49,504 --> 00:50:52,090
Meanwhile, your management control
would be protected.

759
00:50:53,508 --> 00:50:54,634
<i>If he continues to hold out,</i>

760
00:50:54,718 --> 00:50:58,263
we'll take over Hanmin
with a surprise court receivership filing

761
00:50:58,346 --> 00:51:00,307
and spruce it up to sell it.

762
00:51:00,891 --> 00:51:04,144
Then all of Yeouido
will be in the palm of our hands.

763
00:51:08,273 --> 00:51:11,568
The 15th presidential election
is coming up.

764
00:51:12,778 --> 00:51:15,363
They say the nation is in crisis,

765
00:51:15,447 --> 00:51:19,868
but whoever becomes the next president
will have to stimulate the economy.

766
00:51:19,951 --> 00:51:23,121
The IMF crisis
will last four years at most.

767
00:51:23,622 --> 00:51:25,540
Even if all the other companies crumble,

768
00:51:25,624 --> 00:51:28,794
we just need to hold out until then.

769
00:51:30,295 --> 00:51:32,881
At the end of the day,
they would never dare

770
00:51:32,964 --> 00:51:36,134
to go after Hanmin
with just 300 billion won.

771
00:51:37,427 --> 00:51:38,470
That's right.

772
00:51:40,472 --> 00:51:41,848
All right then.

773
00:51:45,602 --> 00:51:46,645
Restructuring?

774
00:51:46,728 --> 00:51:49,815
Dad, there are only four of us
in Risk Management, including me.

775
00:51:49,898 --> 00:51:51,608
It makes it that much easier.

776
00:51:51,691 --> 00:51:53,235
Save yourself and Bang Jin-mok,

777
00:51:53,860 --> 00:51:55,487
and get rid of the other two.

778
00:51:55,570 --> 00:51:57,614
I can't do that. I don't want to.

779
00:51:57,697 --> 00:51:59,366
You know, I realized today

780
00:51:59,449 --> 00:52:02,536
that we need to be closer
to President Shin.

781
00:52:02,619 --> 00:52:04,371
As opinion leaders of this company,

782
00:52:04,454 --> 00:52:06,248
we need to expand our global network.

783
00:52:06,331 --> 00:52:08,124
Knock yourself out being global.

784
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:10,168
I don't want to.

785
00:52:10,752 --> 00:52:11,711
You punk.

786
00:52:11,795 --> 00:52:14,714
This is important stuff,
so at least pretend to listen.

787
00:52:14,798 --> 00:52:15,632
Hey!

788
00:52:24,558 --> 00:52:26,184
A 40% staff reduction?

789
00:52:26,852 --> 00:52:29,437
The president summoned
all the general managers

790
00:52:29,521 --> 00:52:32,482
and told us we had to
reduce our teams by 40 percent.

791
00:52:33,525 --> 00:52:36,152
That overseas investor
who's lending the money

792
00:52:36,236 --> 00:52:37,988
is strongly demanding it,

793
00:52:38,613 --> 00:52:39,948
so there's no other choice.

794
00:52:40,532 --> 00:52:42,576
Was that why Big Al was called in?

795
00:52:42,659 --> 00:52:43,827
Probably.

796
00:52:43,910 --> 00:52:47,497
I heard the division heads
have to decide and submit a layoff list.

797
00:52:48,957 --> 00:52:52,377
And I guess Ms. Hong
may have heard about it sooner.

798
00:52:53,420 --> 00:52:55,005
She already handed in her resignation.

799
00:52:55,797 --> 00:52:57,632
That's the best news I've heard all day.

800
00:52:57,716 --> 00:52:58,967
You're a general manager, so--

801
00:52:59,050 --> 00:53:00,594
Right, so act like one?

802
00:53:00,677 --> 00:53:01,511
Yeah.

803
00:53:16,860 --> 00:53:18,570
{\an8}GENERAL MANAGER CHA JUNG-IL

804
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:26,411
{\an8}WORKFORCE REDUCTION LIST:
RESEARCH DIVISION

805
00:53:44,220 --> 00:53:46,348
WORKFORCE REDUCTION LIST: TRADING DIVISION

806
00:54:29,057 --> 00:54:31,851
An employee with 25 years of service
came to say farewell,

807
00:54:31,935 --> 00:54:33,687
and they have him waiting for three hours?

808
00:55:30,326 --> 00:55:31,494
The chairman said

809
00:55:32,537 --> 00:55:35,081
there is no need for you
to submit your resignation letter.

810
00:55:35,874 --> 00:55:39,002
Today will be
your last day of work, Mr. So.

811
00:55:41,129 --> 00:55:45,633
There's something I'd like to say
to the chairman before I go.

812
00:55:46,217 --> 00:55:47,260
You should just go.

813
00:55:48,762 --> 00:55:49,596
You know how he is.

814
00:56:38,103 --> 00:56:39,604
Mr. Cha,

815
00:56:40,146 --> 00:56:43,399
why don't you finish up
Trading's restructuring list

816
00:56:43,483 --> 00:56:44,818
for me as well?

817
00:56:46,736 --> 00:56:47,570
Yes, sir.

818
00:56:47,654 --> 00:56:49,572
I'll see to it immediately
and report back.

819
00:56:49,656 --> 00:56:50,573
All right.

820
00:56:56,037 --> 00:56:58,748
{\an8}WORKFORCE REDUCTION LIST: TRADING DIVISION
SO GYEONG-DONG

821
00:57:09,425 --> 00:57:11,177
WORKFORCE REDUCTION LIST:
RISK MANAGEMENT DIVISION

822
00:57:11,261 --> 00:57:14,681
ALBERT OH, DIVISION MANAGER: POOR ATTITUDE
BANG JIN-MOK, MANAGER: POOR ATTITUDE

823
00:57:17,892 --> 00:57:20,812
ORGANIZATIONAL RESTRUCTURING NOTICE

824
00:57:24,649 --> 00:57:26,151
RISK MANAGEMENT DIVISION: DISSOLVED

825
00:57:26,234 --> 00:57:27,777
TO BE CONSOLIDATED WITH TRADING DIVISION

826
00:57:27,861 --> 00:57:29,446
Risk Management is being dissolved?

827
00:57:30,071 --> 00:57:31,072
Then where do I go?

828
00:57:31,156 --> 00:57:32,365
ALBERT OH
LEE YONG-GI

829
00:57:32,449 --> 00:57:34,534
Big Al, you're the head of Trading now.

830
00:57:34,617 --> 00:57:35,952
What am I supposed to do there?

831
00:57:36,911 --> 00:57:37,745
No clue.

832
00:57:38,455 --> 00:57:39,747
What am I supposed to do in IT?

833
00:57:39,831 --> 00:57:42,250
Why am I not on the layoff list?

834
00:57:43,626 --> 00:57:46,337
"Pending reassignment
for all entry-level female employees"?

835
00:57:51,134 --> 00:57:52,469
BANG JIN-MOK

836
00:58:03,062 --> 00:58:06,483
ENDURE, EVEN SUFFERING CAN BE BEAUTIFUL.
WHEN HARDSHIP STRIKES, TRY SMILING.

837
00:58:06,566 --> 00:58:09,944
Are you certain about letting go of
Mr. Bang Jin-mok and Mr. So Gyeong-dong

838
00:58:10,028 --> 00:58:11,279
at this time?

839
00:58:11,362 --> 00:58:13,740
It would've been another headache

840
00:58:13,823 --> 00:58:15,492
if they'd refused to leave.

841
00:58:16,284 --> 00:58:18,620
We might as well cut them loose now.

842
00:58:19,370 --> 00:58:22,040
There will always be
younger and smarter new hires.

843
00:58:32,383 --> 00:58:34,260
How could they get rid of Risk Management

844
00:58:34,344 --> 00:58:36,262
when we're in the middle of
the IMF crisis?

845
00:58:37,263 --> 00:58:39,974
And why is Mr. Bang on the layoff list?

846
00:58:40,058 --> 00:58:41,142
I told you I was quitting.

847
00:58:42,101 --> 00:58:43,895
Mr. Bang made me.

848
00:58:43,978 --> 00:58:46,898
He made me write my name down
because I'll never get fired,

849
00:58:46,981 --> 00:58:50,568
and then his own name
since the company's wanted him long gone.

850
00:58:51,152 --> 00:58:52,237
Then three would survive.

851
00:58:55,073 --> 00:58:58,076
I've been wanting to leave Hanmin
for a while now.

852
00:58:58,576 --> 00:59:00,036
If I get forced out,

853
00:59:01,704 --> 00:59:03,289
it'd only leave regrets, right?

854
00:59:04,207 --> 00:59:06,543
Then for your farewell party,

855
00:59:06,626 --> 00:59:08,002
we should go to your favorite--

856
00:59:08,086 --> 00:59:08,920
Forget it.

857
00:59:10,338 --> 00:59:11,881
Let me go home sober for once.

858
00:59:22,850 --> 00:59:24,519
I didn't want to put
your name down anyway.

859
00:59:26,104 --> 00:59:27,772
We still have work to do.

860
00:59:37,949 --> 00:59:43,788
{\an8}HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

861
00:59:46,541 --> 00:59:49,168
Gosh, Yeouido…

862
00:59:54,048 --> 00:59:56,342
What a nasty, unbearable place it's been.

863
00:59:59,429 --> 01:00:00,263
What are you doing?

864
01:00:01,806 --> 01:00:03,516
All right. Jeez.

865
01:00:04,183 --> 01:00:05,059
It's okay.

866
01:00:06,978 --> 01:00:07,812
It's…

867
01:00:08,771 --> 01:00:11,065
All right now.

868
01:00:12,400 --> 01:00:13,318
You did well.

869
01:00:14,068 --> 01:00:14,902
Good work.

870
01:00:19,657 --> 01:00:20,992
Let's part ways here.

871
01:00:21,576 --> 01:00:22,410
That's it.

872
01:00:22,952 --> 01:00:24,621
At least say a few parting words.

873
01:00:36,132 --> 01:00:37,133
Good luck.

874
01:00:42,263 --> 01:00:43,139
Show respect to your senior.

875
01:00:45,058 --> 01:00:46,184
Senior?

876
01:00:51,814 --> 01:00:52,690
I'm off.

877
01:00:55,109 --> 01:00:55,943
Get home safe.

878
01:01:26,724 --> 01:01:27,558
SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

879
01:01:27,642 --> 01:01:28,518
This way.

880
01:01:29,769 --> 01:01:30,728
Watch the steps.

881
01:01:35,525 --> 01:01:36,734
Watch the steps.

882
01:01:40,738 --> 01:01:42,740
Are they moving out of the dorms?

883
01:01:43,241 --> 01:01:44,742
They've been laid off,

884
01:01:45,618 --> 01:01:47,787
so they can no longer stay
in the workers' dormitory.

885
01:01:48,996 --> 01:01:51,541
Many of them go back home
to the countryside.

886
01:02:31,998 --> 01:02:33,374
Bom, wake up.

887
01:02:35,376 --> 01:02:38,171
Let's get changed
and sleep with me in the big room.

888
01:03:11,412 --> 01:03:12,997
PARK JIN-HUI

889
01:03:18,127 --> 01:03:19,337
PARK JIN-HUI
SAENARA BANK

890
01:03:27,094 --> 01:03:28,137
{\an8}HANMIN'S OUTSTANDING WOMEN…

891
01:03:36,270 --> 01:03:38,189
I made those.

892
01:03:50,535 --> 01:03:51,410
<i>Yehppee!</i>

893
01:03:55,331 --> 01:03:56,791
<i>Yehppee and I</i>

894
01:03:56,874 --> 01:03:59,293
<i>are getting the ledger together</i>
<i>for whistleblowing purposes.</i>

895
01:03:59,877 --> 01:04:01,254
<i>You can pick up the slush fund ledger</i>

896
01:04:01,337 --> 01:04:05,091
<i>at the president's office</i>
<i>on the 12th floor in Hanmin's head office.</i>

897
01:04:06,217 --> 01:04:07,176
{\an8}QUARTERLY BUSINESS PLAN

898
01:04:07,760 --> 01:04:09,762
- Is it not there?
- This can't be.

899
01:04:09,846 --> 01:04:11,889
I'll find Yehppee within three months

900
01:04:11,973 --> 01:04:14,475
and retrieve the slush fund ledger.

901
01:04:14,559 --> 01:04:15,476
What?

902
01:04:15,560 --> 01:04:17,770
You already know, Yehppee.

903
01:04:17,854 --> 01:04:20,356
You have a copy
of the slush fund ledger, don't you?

904
01:04:20,940 --> 01:04:21,774
No.

905
01:04:22,733 --> 01:04:23,734
Where's that notebook?

906
01:04:23,818 --> 01:04:25,027
The notebook with the sticker.

907
01:04:25,736 --> 01:04:27,321
Sir, have you seen a notebook this big?

908
01:04:27,405 --> 01:04:29,657
There's a dog sticker
in the bottom-right corner.

909
01:04:29,740 --> 01:04:31,492
I burned it all up already.

910
01:04:32,618 --> 01:04:33,911
See? It's all gone.

911
01:04:38,416 --> 01:04:40,001
<i>Yehppee!</i>

912
01:05:10,823 --> 01:05:12,742
That's an obscene amount of money.

913
01:05:13,534 --> 01:05:15,286
It's three times what we estimated.

914
01:05:24,295 --> 01:05:25,630
Director Yun, I found it.

915
01:05:26,297 --> 01:05:27,465
The slush fund ledger.

916
01:05:40,728 --> 01:05:41,854
Pardon me.

917
01:05:43,356 --> 01:05:44,732
It's all right.

918
01:05:44,815 --> 01:05:46,692
Oh no.

919
01:05:46,776 --> 01:05:48,152
I hope it's okay.

920
01:05:48,819 --> 01:05:49,820
It should be fine.

921
01:05:50,655 --> 01:05:52,698
It's fine. You can go.

922
01:05:52,782 --> 01:05:53,616
Bye.

923
01:06:01,791 --> 01:06:04,335
The higher-ups have no desire
to investigate the slush fund.

924
01:06:05,544 --> 01:06:06,462
They're adamant.

925
01:06:07,713 --> 01:06:09,674
With the economy in crisis,

926
01:06:09,757 --> 01:06:12,134
they can't afford to go after
the executives' corruption.

927
01:06:12,218 --> 01:06:15,596
That's just an excuse
because they're scared.

928
01:06:16,889 --> 01:06:19,016
If it's a national and corporate crisis,

929
01:06:19,684 --> 01:06:21,686
the decision-makers
should take responsibility.

930
01:06:21,769 --> 01:06:25,481
Why are the loyal, hard-working people
losing their jobs and suffering for it?

931
01:06:35,992 --> 01:06:36,867
Damn it.

932
01:07:15,364 --> 01:07:16,574
I wanted to see

933
01:07:17,116 --> 01:07:20,202
if you were someone
who could be entrusted with a life…

934
01:07:21,370 --> 01:07:23,622
for myself.

935
01:07:23,706 --> 01:07:25,583
I'm talking about Hanmin's.

936
01:07:27,084 --> 01:07:30,296
If we go bankrupt, thousands
of employees will be out on the streets.

937
01:07:30,379 --> 01:07:31,881
Is that the justice you seek?

938
01:07:31,964 --> 01:07:34,759
Why haven't you gotten anywhere,
while I've come this far?

939
01:07:34,842 --> 01:07:37,928
I want to do well with this
so I can get a permanent spot next year.

940
01:07:38,012 --> 01:07:39,889
Here's a pick-me-up treat for you.

941
01:07:39,972 --> 01:07:42,558
I am Kim Mi-sook
from Hanmin's Magang Branch.

942
01:07:56,530 --> 01:07:58,616
KIM MI-SOOK
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

943
01:08:09,627 --> 01:08:12,129
{\an8}MOYUN HOSPITAL

944
01:08:24,683 --> 01:08:25,851
Let's talk outside.

945
01:08:26,894 --> 01:08:27,770
Your outfit…

946
01:08:28,646 --> 01:08:29,480
Are you going somewhere?

947
01:08:30,439 --> 01:08:32,942
Today's the day I return to the FSS.

948
01:08:42,409 --> 01:08:43,911
You saw the ledger, so you know.

949
01:08:44,453 --> 01:08:46,163
It's well over 300 billion won.

950
01:08:46,705 --> 01:08:49,291
If Chairman Kang had used that slush fund,

951
01:08:49,875 --> 01:08:52,336
the foreign funding from DK Ventures

952
01:08:52,419 --> 01:08:54,130
and the restructuring
could've been avoided.

953
01:08:54,213 --> 01:08:56,048
Yes, exactly.

954
01:08:56,132 --> 01:08:58,175
I know you think I'm just some vile thief,

955
01:08:58,259 --> 01:09:01,720
but compared to Chairman Kang,
I'm just a petty crook scraping by.

956
01:09:02,304 --> 01:09:03,806
You know what's more infuriating?

957
01:09:03,889 --> 01:09:06,559
Even if this country and Hanmin go under,

958
01:09:06,642 --> 01:09:08,686
Chairman Kang's family
will remain unscathed.

959
01:09:10,396 --> 01:09:13,607
The ledger being burned
was the will of the heavens,

960
01:09:13,691 --> 01:09:16,318
so goodbye to you too, Ms. Hong Keum-bo.

961
01:09:17,736 --> 01:09:18,737
What if it didn't burn?

962
01:09:25,995 --> 01:09:28,747
By the will of the heavens,
it ended up in my hands.

963
01:09:31,667 --> 01:09:33,002
Not a chance, Queen Bee.

964
01:09:34,920 --> 01:09:37,089
You'll be laden with honors
if you return with that.

965
01:09:37,756 --> 01:09:38,883
No.

966
01:09:38,966 --> 01:09:40,134
I'm going to steal it all.

967
01:09:41,302 --> 01:09:42,219
Are you in?

968
01:10:26,847 --> 01:10:28,682
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

969
01:10:29,934 --> 01:10:32,102
{\an8}- Goodbye now.
<i>- This country's economy is in peril.</i>

970
01:10:32,186 --> 01:10:34,730
{\an8}<i>Nobody cares about</i>
<i>a chairman embezzling money.</i>

971
01:10:34,813 --> 01:10:36,607
{\an8}<i>They're not going to pursue it!</i>

972
01:10:36,690 --> 01:10:39,193
{\an8}I'm thinking about securing a position
for Ms. Kang at the company.

973
01:10:40,069 --> 01:10:41,278
{\an8}The lowest score on the written exam?

974
01:10:41,362 --> 01:10:42,738
{\an8}It's you? Ma'am?

975
01:10:42,821 --> 01:10:44,907
{\an8}<i>Director Yun told you to return</i>
<i>on December 8th.</i>

976
01:10:44,990 --> 01:10:46,700
{\an8}<i>Why are you still here?</i>

977
01:10:47,618 --> 01:10:49,912
{\an8}<i>She's just being stubborn right now!</i>

978
01:10:49,995 --> 01:10:51,789
{\an8}Steal 300 billion won and then what?

979
01:10:51,872 --> 01:10:53,332
{\an8}<i>I'm not done yet.</i>

980
01:10:54,083 --> 01:10:55,084
{\an8}Is it just me,

981
01:10:55,584 --> 01:10:58,170
{\an8}or do you seem
particularly interested in Hong Jang-mi?

982
01:10:59,421 --> 01:11:04,426
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim

